<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 14 at 2:15PM CDT  by NWS San Angelo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Coleman and
southeastern Runnels Counties through 300 PM CDT...
At 215 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Valera, moving south at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Coleman, Santa Anna, Voss, Gouldbusk, Valera, Leaday, Talpa, Mozelle,
Fisk and Shields.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
